records.addlTxt:
2:21 PM; Case called for Hearing. Defendant Jamel K White in court.  Prosecuting attorney Molly M Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews the case and notes at the last hearing the defendant indicated he needed more time to retain counsel.  Court inquires if the defendant has been able to retain counsel.  Defendant advises he has not and does not plan to retain counsel in this matter.  Court inquires if the defendant has been provided an offer.  State recites the offer on the record.  Defendant would like to accept the offer and resolve the matter without counsel.  Court will provide the defendant with the plea questionnaire and waiver of right to counsel form.  Court takes a break at 2:26 PM to allow time for the defendant to complete the paperwork.

Case recalled at 2:44 PM; all appearances remain the same.  Court conducts colloquy with the defendant regarding his waiver of right to an attorney.  Court finds the defendant is knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waiving his right to an attorney in this matter.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Court notes based on information provided by the State as well as the defendant the Court believes the defendant may want to retain counsel in this matter.  Court inquires if the prior record will make any changes with respect to the offer.  State is not sure and also believes the defendant should maybe retain counsel.  Court believes based on the issues it would be best to not proceed with the plea and have the defendant obtain counsel.  Court provides the defendant with the petition for court appointed attorney.
Court takes another break at 2:57 PM to allow time for the defendant to complete the petition.

Case recalled at 3:18 PM; all appearances remain the same.  Court reviews the petition for court appointed attorney.  Court will approve the petition and orders repayment at $100.00/month with the first payment due by 11/15/2022.  Court will adjourn for status of counsel.
Hearing scheduled for December 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

1:40 PM; Case called for Hearing.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo. Defendant Jamel K White in court. Court reviews the case on the record and inquires if the defendant plans to retain counsel.  Defendant advises he plans to retain counsel and needs more time to do so.  Defendant advises he plans to retain private counsel.  Court will adjourn for one more status of counsel date and will expect the defendant appears with counsel at the next court date.
Hearing scheduled for October 24, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. Cash bail previously posted to be refunded to poster. Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms. (EXCEPTION: If the Defendant has any firearms in the home, they are to be locked up and the Defendant can not go armed to any place.  Also, the defendant can possess a firearm ONLY if enrolled in a State Certified CCW class).

9:46 AM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Niki Kane. Defendant Jamel K White in court. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. 
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. 
Court advises of right to an attorney. 
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
